name: Dry Land
description:
The King felt cold and in a lot of pain. He moved his arms. It was hard to move he was wet and cold. He could hear and feel his teeth chattering. As he opened his eyes he could see sand and what looked like rocks and trees. His vision was blurred, he rolled over and then could see blue sky and clouds. Where was he, he thought. "where's my children! where's my children?"

Jan 10th
